President Joe Biden has issued an executive order to continue or reestablish various advisory committees until September 30, 2023. The order lists numerous committees in different departments and agencies, including the Committee for the Preservation of the White House, President's Committee on the National Medal of Science, Federal Advisory Council on Occupational Safety and Health, President's Export Council, and many others. The order also specifies that the functions of the President under the Federal Advisory Committee Act will be performed by the respective department or agency heads. Additionally, the order supersedes certain provisions of previous executive orders and makes amendments to others. The order will take effect on September 30, 2021.